        <abstract> 
<p>Much interested in MTM’s lecture at Royal Institution ["On the relation between the abnormal and normal formations in plants", <hi rend="italic">Notes Proc. R. Inst. G. B.</hi> 3 (1860): 223–7].</p>  
<p>Asks for information about crossing of varieties of peas. Describes his own experimental results: "the offspring out of the same pod, instead of being intermediate, was very nearly like the two <hi rend="italic">pure</hi> parents; yet in one, there was a trace of the cross &amp; the next generation showed still more plainly their mongrel origins".</p> 
        </abstract>
